{"data": {"作者": "Lee Cooper, Olcay Sertel, Jun Kong, Gerard Lozanski, Kun Huang, Metin Gurcan", "发表日期": "2009/12/1", "期刊": "Computer methods and programs in biomedicine", "卷号": "96", "期号": "3", "页码范围": "182-192", "出版商": "Elsevier", "简介": "Follicular lymphoma (FL) is the second most common type of non-Hodgkin’s lymphoma. Manual histological grading of FL is subject to remarkable inter- and intra-reader variations. A promising approach to grading is the development of a computer-assisted system that improves consistency and precision. Correlating information from adjacent slides with different stain types requires establishing spatial correspondences between the digitized section pair through a precise non-rigid image registration. However, the dissimilar appearances of the different stain types challenges existing registration methods.", "引用总数": "被引用次数：50", "学术搜索中的文章": "L Cooper, O Sertel, J Kong, G Lozanski, K Huang… - Computer methods and programs in biomedicine, 2009"}, "url": "https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0169260709001588"}
{"data": {"作者": "Matthew Brand, Kun Huang", "发表日期": "2003/1/3", "研讨会论文": "AISTATS", "简介": "Spectral methods use selected eigenvectors of a data affinity matrix to obtain a data representation that can be trivially clustered or embedded in a low-dimensional space. We present a theorem that explains, for broad classes of affinity matrices and eigenbases, why this works: For successively smaller eigenbases (ie, using fewer and fewer of the affinity matrixs dominant eigenvalues and eigenvectors), the angles between similar vectors in the new representation shrink while the angles between dissimilar vectors grow. Specifically, the sum of the squared cosines of the angles is strictly increasing as the dimensionality of the representation decreases. Thus spectral methods work because the truncated eigenbasis amplifies structure in the data so that any heuristic postprocessing is more likely to succeed. We use this result to construct a nonlinear dimensionality reduction (NLDR) algorithm for data sampled from manifolds whose intrinsic coordinate system has linear and cyclic axes, and a novel clustering-by-projections algorithm that requires no postprocessing and gives superior performance on challenge problems from the recent literature.", "引用总数": "被引用次数：157", "学术搜索中的文章": "M Brand, K Huang - AISTATS, 2003"}, "url": "http://www.merl.com/reports/docs/TR2002-42.pdf"}
{"data": {"作者": "Kun Huang, Andrew Wagner, Yi Ma", "发表日期": "2004/12/17", "研讨会论文": "2004 43rd IEEE Conference on Decision and Control (CDC)(IEEE Cat. No. 04CH37601)", "卷号": "3", "页码范围": "3227-3234", "出版商": "IEEE", "简介": "This paper considers the offline identification of hybrid linear time-invariant (LTI) systems that are based on state-space models. This includes the identification of the number of LTI systems involved, the orders of the systems, and the switching times. By embedding the input/output data in a higher dimensional space, the problem of finding the switching times of the hybrid system becomes one of segmenting the data into distinct subspaces. Since these subspaces correspond to the original linear systems, their number and dimension must be found automatically. We examine and compare two different embedding methods. One is based on the well-known subspace method and the other is based on a direct input/output relationship. A robust and deterministic generalized principal component analysis (GPCA) algorithm is presented to solve the multiple-subspace identification problem. In addition, we show that data …", "引用总数": "被引用次数：50", "学术搜索中的文章": "K Huang, A Wagner, Y Ma - 2004 43rd IEEE Conference on Decision and Control …, 2004"}, "url": "https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/1428971/"}
