{"data": {"作者": "Kun Huang, Yi Ma, René Vidal", "发表日期": "2004/6/27", "研讨会论文": "Proceedings of the 2004 IEEE Computer Society Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition, 2004. CVPR 2004.", "卷号": "2", "页码范围": "II-II", "出版商": "IEEE", "简介": "We propose a robust model selection criterion for mixtures of subspaces called minimum effective dimension (MED). Previous information-theoretic model selection criteria typically assume that data can be modelled with a parametric model of certain (possibly differing) dimension and a known error distribution. However, for mixtures of subspaces with different dimensions, a generalized notion of dimensionality is needed and hence introduced in this paper. The proposed MED criterion minimizes this geometric dimension subject to a given error tolerance (regardless of the noise distribution). Furthermore, combined with a purely algebraic approach to clustering mixtures of subspaces, namely the generalized PCA (GPCA), the MED is designed to also respect the global algebraic and geometric structure of the data. The result is a non-iterative algorithm called robust GPCA that estimates from noisy data an unknown …", "引用总数": "被引用次数：64", "学术搜索中的文章": "K Huang, Y Ma, R Vidal - Proceedings of the 2004 IEEE Computer Society …, 2004"}, "url": "https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/1315223/"}
